<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOR COZIER READING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Did you know that 17% of all relationships fail because of disputes over how 
late one partner reads in bed with the lights on? 
</P>
<P>
 Not really, we made that up. But reading after bedtime ranks right up there 
with the major cohabitational irritants. In our experience, no standing, 
suspended or wall-mounted reading light really keeps the peace as well as the 
little book-mounted lights that shine on the page and nowhere else. The 
granddaddy in this genre is the Itty-Bitty Booklight, but the latest is the 
NiteOwl, above, a lamp so slender that it doubles as a bookmark. Available at 
bookstores, from the Sharper Image stores, or by phoning Lumatec Industries at 
(800) 776-7945.  
</P>
</TEXT>
