<P>
TAX FORM IS IN THE MAIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Your 1994 tax forms are in the mail. But you won't get them until after the 
holidays.They are coming as third-class mail. 
</P>
<P>
 The U.S. Postal Service plans to hold the packages at its local offices, with 
carriers being told not to deliver them until Jan. 3. 
</P>
