<P>
SOCIAL CLIMES / THE BUZZ: GAMBLING FOR GOOD, NOT EVIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By COMPILED BY THE SOCIAL CLIMES STAFF 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sin City may never be the same. The new Hard Rock Hotel & Casino in Las Vegas 
has installed -- drum roll please -- politically correct slot machines.(Its 
words are "the world's first socially responsible and morally conscious" slot 
machines.) 
</P>
<P>
 Here's how it works: The money you lose will be donated to the Natural 
Resources Defense Council, Conservation International and Sting's Rainforest 
Foundation. 
</P>
<P>
 Of course, what you do with your winnings is still up to you.  
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Mama's Pearls: With only 154 shopping days left till Mother's Day, we thought 
you should know about a one-of-a-kind gift: a handwritten letter from Bette 
Davis to her daughter, B.D. Hyman, on Hyman's 21st birthday. The five-page 
dispatch, estimated to be worth between $200 and $400, will be on view along 
with other items from Hyman's collection (including her mother's christening 
dress) at Sotheby's in Beverly Hills on Tuesday and Wednesday. The auction is 
Dec. 19 in New York. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Financed Romance: Warren and Annette probably won't be among the thrilled, but 
the Grill has put together quite the romantic New Year's Eve-delivered dinner 
baskets for stay-at-home types. Included with the four-course meal and bottle 
of wine is a videotape for all lovey-dovey couch potatoes -- "An Affair to 
Remember," the 1957 classic that inspired the Beattys' current, although not 
terribly successful, remake, "Love Affair." The price tag: $150 for two. 
</P>
