<TEXT>
<P>
 An assistant professor of English literature at Loyola Marymount University 
has been awarded a $5,000 grant to study Irish writers. 
</P>
<P>
 John Menaghan, who is also writing a contemporary novel on the political 
troubles in Ireland, will begin his studies abroad next summer. 
</P>
