<HEADLINE>
<P>
JUST THE FACTS; HOLIDAY TRAVEL TIPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ship holiday gifts ahead of time. 
</P>
<P>
 * Take an empty suitcase to pack gifts for the return trip. 
</P>
<P>
 * Remember: a direct flight is not always a nonstop flight. 
</P>
<P>
 * Dress for duress: Wear flat-soled, lace-up shoes so you can loosen them if 
your feet swell. 
</P>
<P>
 * On the plane, use a rolled-up blanket for lumbar support and a pillow for 
neck support. If you can, rest your feet on a carry-on bag or a blanket. 
</P>
<P>
 * Arrive at the airport at least an hour before departure to allow for 
congestion and to avoid being bumped. 
</P>
<P>
 * Order special airline meals in advance. 
</P>
<P>
 * Put luggage tags inside and outside your bags and lock your luggage. If you 
check bags, use a carry on for a toothbrush, prescription glasses and 
medications and a change of underwear,anything you must have if your bags go 
missing. 
</P>
