<HEADLINE>
<P>
RIO CRUISE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 My husband and I took the cruise from Buenos Aires to San Juan, Puerto Rico, 
on the Crystal Harmony ("Shipboard Samba Down to Rio," Oct. 2). Everything 
Shirley Slater and Harry Basch reported in their article was accurate and we 
also enjoyed the trip.However, our experience at the Carnival in Rio de Janeiro 
was not the delight we expected (especially at $180 each), and I really laughed 
when I read, "Security at the stadium is well enforced, and you're sitting 
among your fellow cruise ship passengers in a reserved area."  
</P>
<P>
 After the buses dropped us off at the Sambodromo, the tour leader asked us to 
follow him into the stadium so he could show us to our seats. What a sight! 
Thousands of people were jostling and pushing trying to find any seat, let 
alone their "reserved" one. The tour leader pointed to a certain section, told 
us to look for our seats and then he left us. It was absolutely impossible to 
find our assigned seats since they were all taken. Some of the people from the 
ship left, but we decided to stay, so we jostled, shoved and pushed, too, until 
we found two spaces. To add to the discomfort of the evening, it was raining, 
hot and humid.  
</P>
<P>
 Would I recommend this excursion to the Carnival? Yes, but people should be 
warned of what can happen. We enjoyed the experience -- it was breathtakingly 
beautiful. 
</P>
<P>
 NAOMI BRILL 
</P>
<P>
 Pacific Palisades 
</P>
