</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A benefit performance of "Awake and Sing!" for Crenshaw High's student-run 
business, Food From the 'Hood, will take place today at 4 p.m. at the Bergamot 
Station Arts Center, 2525 Michigan Ave. in Santa Monica.  
</P>
<P>
 The critically acclaimed revival of Clifford Odets'play, starring Orson Bean, 
follows the trials of a Jewish family living on the brink of poverty during the 
Depression.The benefit performance is in conjunction with the Bergamot Station 
Art Center's Winterfest Party, which features art, music and theatrical 
performances. 
</P>
<P>
 All proceeds will benefit Food From the 'Hood and the Odyssey Theatre 
Ensemble. Food From the 'Hood makes its own salad dressing to raise money for 
college scholarships. The group regularly donates 25% of its harvest to the 
needy. 
