 Manual Arts 1, Venice 1 -- Sloppy defensive work in the second half forced a 
tie between the Coastal Conference teams. 
</P>
<P>
 Forward Arturo Piedra knocked a rebound off a Venice defender to give the 
Toilers a 1-0 halftime lead. However, the Toilers (1-2-1) were not so fortunate 
in the second half as Venice scored on a kick from midfield. 
</P>
<P>
 Narbonne 3, Dorsey 0 -- Jorge Garcia scored twice from inside the penalty box 
as the Gauchos defeated the visiting Dongs in a Southern Pacific Conference 
match. 
</P>
<P>
 Lack of communication between Dorsey sweeper Marvin Gonzalez and goalie Frank 
Figeroa proved critical as Garcia was able to convert turnovers into goals. 
</P>
