<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEPPERDINE LOSES FIFTH IN A ROW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Things went from bad to worse for Pepperdine's basketball team Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
 The Waves committed 28 turnovers and lost to Boise State, 74-53, in a 
nonconference game at Boise, Ida. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the fifth loss in a row for Pepperdine (1-5), the team's longest losing 
streak since a six-game skid in 1986-87. 
</P>
<P>
 The start is Pepperdine's worst since the 1973-74 season. 
</P>
<P>
 Only two Pepperdine players scored in double figures. Junior center Gavin 
Vanderputten scored 13 points, and sophomore guard Gerald Brown had 10. 
</P>
<P>
 Boise State's All-Big Sky center John Coker, meanwhile, had 21 points and 
eight rebounds. Sophomore forward J.D. Huleen had 14 points and senior guard 
Sherman Morris 10 for the Broncos. 
</P>
<P>
 Boise State (4-1) led only 29-23 at halftime, but outscored the Waves, 45-30, 
in the second half. 
</P>
</TEXT>
