<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; GOTTLIEB LEADS TUSTIN PAST TRABUCO HILLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RICK CHRISTOPHER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Doug Gottlieb sparked Tustin's 52-point, second-half performance as the 
Tillers beat Trabuco Hills, 89-70, in the championship game of the In-N-Out 
Burger/Converse Classic Saturday at Capistrano Valley High. 
</P>
<P>
 Gottlieb, named the tournament most valuable player, scored 14 points in the 
second quarter and finished with 20. 
</P>
<P>
 "Tustin's defensive pressure was there from the outset," Trabuco Hills Coach 
Rainer Wolf said. "We had too many turnovers, and it disrupted our flow." 
</P>
<P>
 Trabuco Hills took an 11-5 lead behind Nick Punto's three-pointer, and 
increased it to 14-7 on Laquent Fobbs' three-pointer. 
</P>
<P>
 "We have some lightning-powered offense, and we can score in bunches," Wolf 
said. "But the turnovers quickly took us out of our rhythm." 
</P>
<P>
 Tustin center David Lalazarian had 21 points and 12 rebounds. His quick outlet 
passes set up easy baskets by Aaron Krause, who finished with 18. 
</P>
<P>
 Trabuco Hills managed to cut Tustin's lead to three at 51-48 with 2 minutes 35 
seconds remaining in the third quarter on Jonathon Paisley's jumper. 
</P>
<P>
 A 14-6 run by Tustin quickly widened the lead to 65-48. 
</P>
<P>
 Paisley led Trabuco Hills with 19 points, followed by Rob Warnick's 16. RICK 
CHRISTOPHER 
</P>
</TEXT>
