<TEXT>
<P>
 In the El Toro 10-Way tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Anaheim wins -- Anaheim, ranked sixth in the county, upset third-ranked Laguna 
Hills to win at El Toro High. 
</P>
<P>
 Anaheim, finishing 8-0 in dual competition, defeated Laguna Hills, 38-16, in 
the last dual match of the tournament.Both teams were 7-0 before they competed. 
</P>
<P>
 Jose Lopez (103), Alexei Yanuaria (130), Manny Megia (135) and brothers Robert 
(171) and Reuben Droughns (189) won their respective weight classes. 
</P>
<P>
 "They just kicked our fannies," Laguna Hills Coach Cliff Jarmie said. "We have 
no excuses. We just have to work harder." 
</P>
<P>
 Thanh Nguyen (119), Scott Morinoue (140) and Casey Elliott (160) won their 
weight classes for Laguna Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 Finishing third behind Laguna Hills was San Clemente at 6-2. Adam Miller (145) 
and Aaron Greco (152), who was named most valuable wrestler in the upper 
weights, were champions for San Clemente. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Fullerton tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton wins -- La Puente's Carlos Gutierrez was a top performer in the 
lower division, winning by a pin in 1:45. 
</P>
<P>
 Erick Avalos, also from La Puente, won by pin in 1:24 in the heavyweight 
division. 
