<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; STANFORD ROUTS CAL STATE FULLERTON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Bobbi Kelsey scored 21 points and five other Stanford players scored in double 
figures to lead the fifth-ranked Cardinal to a record-tying 122-80 women's 
basketball victory over visiting Cal State Fullerton on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Center Koko Lahanas -- who made 10 of 16 field-goal attempts and 11 of 12 free 
throws -- scored 31 points for the Titans, who received only one point from 
their reserves. 
</P>
<P>
 Titan guard Shayla Bradshaw scored 20 points and point guard Marissa Frial had 
18. 
</P>
<P>
 Stanford's point total tied a school record set last year against Long Beach 
in a 122-49 victory over the 49ers. Stanford is 4-1. The Titans are 1-3. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonconference men's basketball 
</P>
<P>
 Concordia 96, Whittier College 67 -- Pharoh Jones scored 18 points as the 
Eagles breezed past Whittier College. Jeff Putnam added 15 points and eight 
rebounds for Concordia. Whittier's Justin Snowden had 20 points. 
