<HEADLINE>
<P>
SELECTIVE GIVING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I am writing in response to the recent story about those ignorant people who 
supposedly are good-hearted and want to help others less fortunate than 
themselves. These so-called "good" people will give, but only if their 
donations go to legal residents or English-speaking or those with non-Latino 
surnames.These people are not kind and good, they are bigots. 
</P>
<P>
 I would tell all these people to keep their donations and learn the true 
meaning of giving. True giving comes from the heart, not from politics and 
prejudice, and certainly not from ignorance. 
</P>
<P>
 I give because I consider myself very lucky and want to bring some little bit 
of happiness to someone not as lucky as myself. I don't care what color they 
are, if they speak English or if they are here illegally. I feel sorry for you 
(who) do not know or have in your hearts the true spirit of giving or of the 
season. 
</P>
<P>
 ISABEL DEL POZO 
</P>
<P>
 Anaheim 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
