<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: OXNARD; WOMAN, 3 YOUTHS HELD IN DRUG-DEALING CASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 37-year-old Oxnard woman has been arrested on suspicion of using teen-agers 
to sell heroin and cocaine, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Along with arresting Cecilia Zaragoza Morales, undercover detectives also took 
three juveniles, ages 14 to 16, into custody on suspicion of selling narcotics. 
All of the arrests were made last week. 
</P>
<P>
 The three-month investigation that led to the arrests was part of the Oxnard 
Police Department's Operation Revitalization program. The grant-funded program 
targets youths ages 14 to 18 who are involved in drug- or alcohol-related 
crimes. 
</P>
<P>
 Earlier this year, detectives assigned to Operation Revitalization arrested a 
man who was using his 12-year-old brother to sell drugs out of a south Oxnard 
home. JULIE FIELDS 
