2 INJURED IN SANTA PAULA SHOOTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A reported "gunfight" in Santa Paula on Saturday afternoon sent two men to the 
hospital for gunshot wounds, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 About eight shots were fired in the exchange that occurred about 1:30 p.m. in 
the 500 block of Acacia Road in Santa Paula, a Santa Paula police spokesman 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Alfonso Cerda, 24, of Santa Paula was shot once in the left arm and once in 
the thigh. He was transported to Santa Paula Memorial Hospital where he was 
listed in fair condition, a hospital spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
 Brian Herron, 27, also of Santa Paula, was grazed across the chest by a bullet 
and sought medical treatment on his own at Ventura County Medical Center and 
was then released. Officers later arrested Herron on a parole violation. 
</P>
<P>
 As of late Saturday, police had no further information on the incident and had 
made no more arrests. 
