<HEADLINE>
<P>
ENVIRONMENT: NOTES ABOUT YOUR SURROUNDINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Watch the Birdies--Anyone with avian interests is invited to join in the 95th 
National Christmas Bird Count on Saturday from dawn until sundown. 
</P>
<P>
 Saturday's bird count will concentrate on South County areas, including Doheny 
Beach, the San Juan Creek estuary, Dana Point Harbor and San Clemente. 
</P>
<P>
 Inland areas to be surveyed include Ronald W. Caspers Regional Park, Laguna 
Niguel Regional Park, the Saddleback College area, Aliso/Wood Canyons Regional 
Park and Camp Pendleton.  
</P>
<P>
 Birders will be dispatched to different areas to count different species. It 
is not necessary to be an expert birder; in fact, people of all experience 
levels are encouraged to participate. All birders should bring binoculars and 
bird identification books. 
</P>
<P>
 A section by section report of the count will be included in National 
Audubon's American Birds publication which summarizes all the bird counts 
across the country. 
</P>
<P>
 Bird counts will also be held in other parts of the county this month and in 
January. For more information on Saturday's bird count and other events, call 
South Coast Audubon at (714) 661-7525. For information on bird counts in 
northeast or northwest Orange County, call Sea & Sage Audubon Society at (714) 
261-7963. 
</P>
