<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN IS SHOT BY POLICE DURING CHASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By THAO HUA, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two police officers seriously wounded a man in a shootout early Saturday after 
an 18-mile car chase, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The man, identified as Tayo Valen Bond, 28, whose address was not available, 
was in satisfactory condition later Saturday in the jail ward of Western 
Medical Center Hospital-Anaheim, a spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
 The officers involved in the shooting were not injured. 
</P>
<P>
 A Westminster officer spotted Bond driving erratically near Garden Grove 
Boulevard and the Garden Grove Freeway in Westminster about 1:10 a.m. Saturday, 
police said. When Bond refused to pull over, two officers -- one from 
Westminster and another from the Fullerton Police Department -- pursued him, 
said Fullerton Police Sgt. Danny Becerra. 
</P>
<P>
 About 15 minutes later, the man lost control of his black sports car, which 
spun out, then came to a stop in the 3700 block of West Carol Drive in 
Fullerton, police said. Bond then reportedly abandoned his car and fled on 
foot, pursued by the officers. 
</P>
<P>
 "It was about a block later when he turned around and fired at the two 
officers," Becerra said. "Then the officers returned fire." 
</P>
<P>
 Bond suffered gunshot wounds in the lower torso and right hand and collapsed 
on the ground, Becerra said. He was being held Saturday on suspicion of 
attempted murder of a police officer and evading arrest. 
</P>
