<HEADLINE>
<P>
DEPUTY SHOT IN HEAD DURING TRAFFIC STOP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 29-year-old Walnut station sheriff's deputy was shot in the head Saturday 
while making a traffic stop in Rowland Heights, a sheriff's spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
 The deputy, whose name was not released, was shot just before 6 p.m. in the 
18400 block of La Guardia Street, said Deputy Angie McLaughlin. She declined to 
release other details of the shooting. 
</P>
<P>
 "Neighbors in the area say they heard three gunshots and saw a vehicle 
speeding away from the scene," McLaughlin said, "They called Walnut station 
when they saw a deputy was wounded." 
</P>
<P>
 The deputy was taken to Queen of the Valley Hospital in West Covina, where as 
of late Saturday night he was in extremely critical condition, McLaughlin said. 
</P>
