<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRLS' BASKETBALL / BUENA TOURNAMENT; ALEMANY WORKS OVERTIME TO DEFEAT BUENA 
FOR TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVE DESMOND, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Carly Funicello's six-foot turnaround jump shot with 41 seconds left in 
overtime gave Alemany High a 53-52 victory over Buena in the championship game 
of the Buena tournament Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
 Funicello, the tournament's most valuable player, had 20 points and 10 
rebounds for the Indians (4-0), the state's second-ranked team. 
</P>
<P>
 Teammate Samantha Rigley scored 12 points, while Kelly McKay added 11. 
</P>
<P>
 Buena, which lost its tournament for only the second time in 18 years, was 
paced by Kori Sebek's 19 points. Guard Eboni Conley added 10 for the 
fifth-ranked Bulldogs (2-1). 
</P>
<P>
 The Indians had a chance to win it in regulation, when Rigley was fouled with 
six seconds left and the score tied, 49-49. However, Rigley missed her first 
free throw in seven attempts. 
</P>
<P>
 The Bulldogs had two possessions after Funicello's overtime winner. However, 
both times Buena missed its shots and both times Funicello rebounded. 
</P>
<P>
 Newbury Park 52, Hart 37 -- Jann Thorpe had 13 points and eight rebounds to 
lead Newbury Park (6-1) to third place. Teammate Julie Wastell added 11 points 
and seven rebounds. Renee Intlekofer scored 10 points. 
</P>
<P>
 LaCresha Clark paced Hart (2-2) with 10 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Chatsworth 55, Ventura 53 -- Tynitra Wilson had 14 points and 13 rebounds as 
the Chancellors (4-2) won the consolation championship. Jodi Borenstein scored 
12 points and Shanna Sasaki added 11 points for Chatsworth. 
</P>
<P>
 Jenie Chenoweth and Christine Franklin each scored 12 points for the Cougars 
(1-2). 
</P>
</TEXT>
