<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL FOOTBALL FINALS; MONTCLAIR PREP'S DENT WRECKS ORANGE LUTHERAN; 
SOUTHERN SECTION DIVISION X: QUARTERBACK RUSHES FOR 265 YARDS, SCORES THREE 
TIMES IN 53-13 VICTORY. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FERNANDO DOMINGUEZ, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Many dream of ending their high school careers this way but Darrel Dent now 
knows what it feels like. 
</P>
<P>
 The senior quarterback ran for 265 yards and three touchdowns and passed for 
another to lead Montclair Prep to a 53-13 victory over Orange Lutheran in the 
Southern Section Division X championship game Saturday night at Valley College. 
</P>
<P>
 "Coach (George Giannini) wanted me to go out in fashion," Dent said. "He said 
to go out in style." 
</P>
<P>
 Dent, who had eight carries, was downright dapper in leading the Mounties 
(11-1) to their second section title in three seasons and third since 1990. 
</P>
<P>
 He scored on runs of 91, eight and 42 yards and had a 47-yard touchdown pass 
play as Orange Lutheran (11-3) keyed on stellar running back Akil Anderson. 
</P>
<P>
 "When we motioned our backs, they shifted everyone to that side and we had the 
bootleg open for Darrel," Giannini said. 
</P>
<P>
 Anderson, who had gained 871 yards in the previous three playoff games, still 
rushed for 116 yards in 30 carries and scored twice, including a one-yard run 
in the third quarter when the Mounties scored 20 unanswered points after 
leading, 19-13, at halftime. 
</P>
<P>
 The Mounties took advantage of fumbles by Orange Lutheran's Che Holloway on 
back-to-back kickoff returns to blow the game open in the third quarter. They 
turned both turnovers into scores, the first on the run by Anderson and moments 
later on a four-yard run by Demetrius Green, who also scored in the fourth 
quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Those came after Dent had connected with wide receiver Kenny Peffer on a 
47-yard pass play early in the quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 "Coach told us (at halftime) to go out there and maintain our level of 
consistency and we would be all right," Dent said. 
</P>
<P>
 Orange Lutheran had seven turnovers, including three passes thrown by 
quarterback Joe Juliano that were intercepted by Henry Bell, Langston Woodberry 
and Mark Zone. 
</P>
<P>
 The Mounties got a break right at the start and capitalized on it. 
</P>
<P>
 On the game's first offensive play, Juliano fumbled the snap and linebacker 
Will Tuccio recovered at the Lancer 47-yard line. 
</P>
<P>
 Montclair Prep took eight plays to score, with Anderson capping it with a 
one-yard run. 
</P>
<P>
 The Lancers marched 67 yards in six plays on the ensuing possession, but 
failed in three attempts to to score from the Montclair Prep one-yard line.  
</P>
<P>
 On third and goal from the one, Tuccio and safety Kenny Peffer stopped 
Juliano, and Woodberry stopped Holloway on the next play. 
</P>
<P>
 The Mounties struck quickly after that on a 91-yard sprint along the left 
sideline by Dent for a 13-0 advantage late in the first quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Orange Lutheran pulled to within 13-7 early in the second quarter on a 
three-yard pass from Juliano to tight end Aaron Kenney. 
</P>
<P>
 Juliano was 17 of 33 for 243 yards and two touchdowns. 
</P>
</TEXT>
