<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE: GUTSHALL NAMED PRESIDENT OF PALO ALTO DRUG MAKER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Thomas L. Gutshall will join CV Therapeutics, an emerging biopharmaceutical 
company based on molecular cardiology, as president and chief operating 
officer. He will report to Louis G. Lange, chairman and chief executive. 
Gutshall, 56, will join the Palo Alto firm in January. He was also elected to 
CV's board, effective immediately. He has been executive vice president of 
Syntex Corp. 
</P>
<P>
 Benjamin Benya has been named media director for Chiat/Day in Los Angeles. He 
will be in charge of all the advertising agency's Los Angeles-based accounts 
except Nissan Motors. Benya previously was senior vice president of media and 
broadcast relations at Teleprograms Marketing Inc. 
</P>
<P>
 Robert S. Leff has resigned as co-chairman and senior vice president of 
business development at Merisel Inc. to pursue personal interests. Leff 
co-founded Merisel's predecessor company, Softsel Computer Products Inc., in 
1980. The El Segundo-based company is a leading wholesale distributor of 
microcomputer hardware and software products. Leff said he had been planning 
his retirement for six months and the timing seemed right. 
</P>
<P>
 Doug Murphy has been appointed vice president of the Walt Disney Gallery, a 
unit of the Disney Store Inc. in Glendale. Murphy joined the Disney Store in 
September, 1991, as manager of new business development. In April, 1993, he was 
named to head business development of the Disney Store, a unit Walt Disney Co., 
Burbank. 
</P>
<P>
 Donald C. De Vore has joined Pasadena-based Right Associates as vice president 
of client services at the human resources consulting firm. De Vore was 
previously founder and president of the Corporate Executive Outplacement Group 
in Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
 E for M Corp. has appointed Ian G. Walker senior vice president and chief 
financial officer. Before joining the Torrance-based cardiology equipment and 
supply company, Walker was vice president-Finance Europe for ICN BioMedicals 
Inc. in Costa Mesa. 
</P>
<P>
 Louis A. Kwiker has joined Bristol Farms Gourmet Specialty Food Markets as 
chairman and chief executive in a change in ownership. The current owner and 
president, Irv Gronsky, will continue to participate in daily operations of the 
Torrance-based firm as vice chairman. Kwiker has operated as a retail 
consultant for Kidd, Kamm & Co. since 1993. He is the former president and CEO 
of Wherehouse Entertainment Inc. 
</P>
<P>
 Matthew Chan has joined Novellus Systems Inc. as president of Novellus Asia, a 
new position. He reports to Peter Hanley, executive vice president sales and 
marketing. Chan is responsible for all of the San Jose firm's operations on the 
Asian mainland including Singapore and Taiwan. Most recently he was operations 
manager for Tektronix Inc.'s Asia southeast operations where he was responsible 
for the development of sales, training and distribution centers in Hong Kong, 
Singapore and China. Novellus Systems Inc. manufactures, markets and services 
advanced automated wafer fabrication systems for chemical vapor deposition of 
thin films. 
</P>
<P>
 Bar-Master International of Los Angeles has announced the appointment of 
Terence D. Crouch as president and chief executive of its Bar-Master and 
Condiment-Master operations. Crouch previously held positions with Unilever and 
FMC in Europe, and with Groen, Jackson Products and Multiplex in the United 
States. 
</P>
<P>
 Joel Suarez has been named vice president and chief financial officer of 
Mission Foods Corp. Suarez previously was vice president of operations, 
planning and development for three years. 
</P>
<P>
 Jay Oken has been promoted to chief financial officer of West Venture Cos. in 
Encino. Oken will be responsible for the financial operations of both the West 
Venture Homes and West Venture Commercial divisions of the company. Oken joined 
West Venture in 1991 as controller. 
</P>
<P>
 Alan Puzarne has been appointed vice president at Los Angeles for Blue Shield 
of California, a new position. Previously, Puzarne was vice president of 
Medi-Cal Systems for FHP Healthcare. 
</P>
