</P>
<P>
 1935: $-0.7 (Two expensive movies flop: "Showboat," "Sutter's Gold") 
</P>
<P>
 1936: $-1.6 (Carl Laemmle Sr. sells out his interest in Universal) 
</P>
<P>
 1937: $-1.0 (First Deanna Durbin picture, "One Hundred Men and a Girl") 
</P>
<P>
