</P>
<P>
 Warner Bros. enjoyed skyrocketing profits from its early talkies in the late 
1920s. But its finances suffered from the Depression in the early '30s and 
recovery was slow. Its profit margin was about $10,000 per picture in 1935. 
Booming attendance boosted profits again in the mid-40s. 
</P>
