<HEADLINE>
<P>
STYLE: FASHION; THE DATE BEFORE CHRISTMAS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 'Tis a night before Christmas, and I must dress for a date... 
</P>
<P>
 With a child who's hungry and a sitter who's late. 
</P>
<P>
 Soon the powder is flying, on his face and mine... 
</P>
<P>
 Then I look in the mirror -- Will I be ready on time? 
</P>
<P>
 Once Tiffany arrives, I lay down the rules. She tries to ignore me, thinking 
she's cool. 
</P>
<P>
 I open the door and finally surmise that this gown's the right gown by the 
look in his eyes. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Produced and styled by Michael Eisenhower and Bob Sparkman 
</P>
